course_title: Women's Health Gender Related Nurse Practitioner Clinical Practicum I
course_description: This course is the first Women's Health Gender Related practicum course where students focus on the delivery of inclusive best practice care to the gynecological patient. Students begin developing clinical reasoning and management skills in an interprofessional healthcare setting.
prerequisites: NRSG 578D prerequisite and 581D co-requisite or equivalent transfer credit. Students must enroll in NRSG 581D first.
